AWS RDS SQL Server High Availability Solution
__________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
Executive Summary Case Study: AWS RDS SQL Server High Availability & Disaster Recovery Architecture

This project implemented a cloud-native high-availability and disaster-recovery architecture using AWS RDS for SQL Server. By leveraging managed Multi-AZ deployments, automated failover, and snapshot-based recovery models, 
The platform achieved service-level resilience, reduced operational complexity, and established a governed, enterprise-grade HA/DR strategy.
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Business Context

The organization operates mission-critical production databases using Amazon Web Services managed services, specifically:

AWS RDS for SQL Server
Managed High Availability configurations
Multi-AZ deployments
Zone-level fault tolerance
Cloud-native resilience engineering
Managed platform operations

The project focused on validating, documenting, and governing a cloud-native HA/DR strategy using managed database services rather than infrastructure-managed clustering models.

